content: Christopher Chope shouted an objection in the Commons causing the motion to be postponed.

title: Minister sorry for Standards Commissioner remarks
content: Kwasi Kwarteng appeared to question whether Kathryn Stone should keep her job amid a row over MPs conduct.

title: Rafiq and Hutton to give evidence to MPs
content: Ex-Yorkshire player Azeem Rafiq and the county's former chair Roger Hutton will give evidence to a Digital, Culture, Media and Sport select committee hearing on Tuesday.

title: HS2 rail extension to Leeds set to be scrapped
content: Plans to extend the eastern leg of the high speed network will be ditched in favour of new shorter links.

title: MoD not aware of any harm after Afghan data breach
content: An inquiry into the mistakes blames "human error", a lack of training and "operational pressure".

title: Kickstart youth jobless plan helps 100,000
content: More than 100,000 young people have started new jobs under the £2bn government scheme, figures show.

title: Government delays education changes by one year
content: Education Secretary Nadhim Zahawi says it would be "wrong to push too hard" on its timetable.
